<h2>When to Use Which</h2>

<h3>Use Claude Code When...</h3>
<ul>
  <li>You're actively writing code and want autocomplete, refactoring, and inline help</li>
  <li>You need instant feedback on syntax, patterns, or library usage</li>
  <li>You're learning a new language or framework and want a tutor in your editor</li>
</ul>

<h3>Use J.A.R.V.I.S. When...</h3>
<ul>
  <li>You need an agent that works <em>for</em> you, not just <em>with</em> you</li>
  <li>You want automation across browsers, desktops, and servers</li>
  <li>You need long-term memory and context that survives across sessions</li>
  <li>You're managing complex workflows (research, content creation, monitoring)</li>
  <li>You want proactive help based on what you're actually doing</li>
</ul>

<h3>Use Both When...</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>You're a developer building projects:</strong> Claude Code helps you write the code. J.A.R.V.I.S. manages deployment, monitors uptime, and handles non-coding tasks.</li>
  <li><strong>You're a content creator:</strong> Claude Code drafts scripts in your editor. J.A.R.V.I.S. schedules posts, monitors analytics, and researches trending topics.</li>
  <li><strong>You're running a startup:</strong> Claude Code accelerates development. J.A.R.V.I.S. manages competitor monitoring, customer outreach, and operational workflows.</li>
</ul>

<h2>The Mental Model</h2>

<p><strong>Claude Code is a tool in your toolbox.</strong> You pick it up when you need it, use it for a specific job, and put it down when you're done.</p>

<p><strong>J.A.R.V.I.S. is your Chief of Staff.</strong> It's always on, always aware, and handles everything you delegate — whether you're at your desk or asleep.</p>

<div class="highlight-box">
<p><strong>Think of it this way:</strong></p>
<p>Claude Code makes you a <em>faster</em> coder.<br/>J.A.R.V.I.S. makes you a <em>more capable</em> human.</p>
</div>

<h2>Why Not Both?</h2>

<p>Here's the thing: <strong>they're complementary</strong>. Use Claude Code inside your editor for real-time coding assistance. Use J.A.R.V.I.S. for everything else — research, automation, monitoring, delegation, memory, and orchestration.</p>

<p>You wouldn't use a hammer to cut wood, and you wouldn't use a saw to drive nails. Same principle here.</p>

<p>Want to see J.A.R.V.I.S. in action? <a href="/docs/installation">Install it</a> and experience autonomous AI for yourself. Want coding help? Keep using Claude Code — it's great at what it does.</p>

<p>The future isn't picking one AI tool. It's orchestrating many. J.A.R.V.I.S. is how you do that.</p>

